

01. While your computer is booting enter a 'DEL' key or 'F2' key 
and enter into BIOS mode. In the BIOS settings try to find out 
how to specify the first boot device as CD-ROM.

02. Boot the computer using DEPIK's DSL CD. While booting from CD, at
the boot prompt (Boot: ) give 'dsl 2' to boot Linux in command line (CLI) 
mode.

03. At the boot prompt (Boot:) press 'Enter' key to boot Linux in GUI mode.

04. Once DSL is booted successful, click terminal icon present in the
upper left corner of desktop and get the terminal window. At the terminal 
window try the various Linux commands given.

05. Using vi editor write hello.c program, compile and run
